e\ncycle. Using the classical self-absorbed jet synchrotron emission model, the\nJED-SAD configuration reproduces also very satisfactorily the radio properties,\nin particular the switch-off and -on events and the radio-X-ray correlation.\nWithin the JED-SAD framework, radio emission can be used to constrain the\nunderlying disk configuration. If this result is confirmed using other\noutbursts from GX 339-4 or other X-ray binaries, then radio could be indeed\nused as another means to indirectly probe disk physics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 May 2019 14:35:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-26"}
